1
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,400
Did you talk to your
Aunt Celeste already?

2
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:22,867
I haven't talked to her yet.

3
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:25,933
I don't need her help anyway.

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,133
It wouldn't hurt if you ask help
from her and her family.

5
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:34,567
They know a lot of people
in Sorsogon who can help you.

6
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,133
Yes, Dad.

7
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,200
You should do your job properly,
Celeste.

8
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:39,967
That's not a product
of Sorsogon.

9
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,433
Yes, Sir.

10
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,867
You've been here for a long time
and that's your only output?

11
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:45,200
You're so fussy.

12
00:00:50,367 --> 00:00:51,433
Focus, Mikoy.

13
00:00:57,567 --> 00:01:00,733
Just for documentation.

14
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,133
I'll send this to Mayor.

15
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,767
Tonito, we've been
waiting for you.

16
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:08,533
- Hi.
- Let's eat

17
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:11,567
and let's welcome
our new shareholder.

18
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:12,600
Who?

19
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:13,867
Me.

20
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:16,000
We are on our way to
the Provincial Capital Building

21
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:19,333
to consult the Provincial
Tourism office

22
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,500
about our project.

23
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:22,767
Next time I'll invite
your Aunt Celeste also.

24
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:23,533
Okay.

25
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,133
Tonito, that's so cruel of you.

26
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:28,867
You saw how happy she was when
she saw you together.

27
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:31,200
That's why I didn't want
to give her false hope.

28
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:34,033
I don't want to put it off now
and deal with it later.

29
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,433
Because what's the point?

30
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:38,033
Celeste and I will get married
in four months.

31
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:39,800
She needs to accept that.

32
00:01:39,867 --> 00:01:42,233
You're a pili vendor?

33
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:45,067
I'm a COO of Pili farm owner.

34
00:01:45,133 --> 00:01:46,367
Just laugh.

35
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,633
You look ugly when you frown.

36
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:49,633
Excuse me.

37
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:53,133
You're uglier, Mr. COO.

38
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,400
Was that Basti?

39
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:55,900
You look happy.

40
00:01:55,967 --> 00:01:58,033
You know he's okay.

41
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:00,067
Maybe we just got
on the wrong foot.

42
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:02,167
Thank you so much
for substituting for me.

43
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:05,867
Take care.

44
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:09,467
Mikoy, don't hurt her.

45
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:11,000
If she behaves, right?

46
00:02:11,067 --> 00:02:13,500
Thank you for saving me today.

47
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,000
Thank you? There's a payment
for that.

48
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:16,100
What do you mean by payment?

49
00:02:17,033 --> 00:02:17,967
What's with you, Mikoy?

50
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:19,067
That's irritating.

51
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:20,100
Don't be like that.

52
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:21,233
I'm getting married.

53
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:23,433
- So?
- You're not funny.

54
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:24,633
What do you think of me?

55
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,000
You know you're dirty-minded.

56
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:27,833
Where will you take me?

57
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:29,033
Just wait.

58
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,300
Grandma Ikay.

59
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:35,800
Celeste, is that you?

60
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:37,033
You're so beautiful.

61
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,033
Let me see.

62
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,567
I missed you.

63
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:41,833
Me too.

64
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:42,900
Let's go upstairs.

65
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:44,433
Come on. Come on.

66
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:52,133
Come in.

67
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:55,900
- Wow, it's like a fiesta.
- Have a seat.

68
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:01,900
Grandma has been asking me
to invite you for days now.

69
00:03:01,967 --> 00:03:05,100
Good thing you decided
to come home.

70
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:08,500
Maybe your father is very
happy to see you, right?

71
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:11,500
Let's eat. I'm already hungry.

72
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:13,233
Okay.

73
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,967
You are still very
beautiful, Celeste.

74
00:03:17,033 --> 00:03:18,400
What's with you, Grandma?

75
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:19,800
You are beautiful.

76
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:20,900
It doesn't fade.

77
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,067
Don't say it loud.

78
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:24,700
The neighbors might hear it.

79
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:28,800
How is your life in Manila?

80
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:30,267
It's okay. It's happy.

81
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:35,167
I'm getting married.

82
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:37,767
I met him in Manila.

83
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:41,133
You and Mikoy are invited.

84
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:45,200
Yes, I heard about
your wedding.

85
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:49,133
Ever since you arrived,
Mikoy always talked about you.

86
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:52,567
I'm not saying
anything, Grandma.

87
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,800
Hmmm.

88
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,767
I'm sure everything he says
is all negative.

89
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:59,333
Oh.

90
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,867
Why? Is there something
positive?

91
00:04:02,667 --> 00:04:04,200
He's very grouchy.

92
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:06,067
I'm just matching
your grouchiness.

93
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:12,433
Hey, is that pinangat ?

94
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,933
Of course.

95
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,967
Wow!

96
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:18,033
I add more chilies to it

97
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:21,400
because I know that spicy
 pinangat is your favorite.

98
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:23,067
That's great.

99
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:25,000
Grandma, she doesn't
eat spicy food anymore.

100
00:04:25,067 --> 00:04:26,500
She's no longer a Sorsoganon.

101
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:28,233
Why?

102
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:29,833
It's not that.

103
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:31,700
It's not that I don't like it.

104
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:33,900
I have hyperacidity.

105
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:36,100
I'm not allowed
to eat spicy food.

106
00:04:36,167 --> 00:04:38,800
But for you, I'll eat.

107
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,400
Oh.

108
00:04:40,467 --> 00:04:43,033
You can't eat
spicy food anymore.

109
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,100
I can.

110
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:46,633
Go ahead.

111
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,267
- Do you want me to?
- Yes.

112
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:52,933
Okay, I'll eat this
but you should eat ten chilies.

113
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,900
Just ten?

114
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:55,100
Yes.

115
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:56,233
Call.

116
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:12,967
Eat some more.

117
00:05:13,033 --> 00:05:14,733
- Mmmm.
- It's ten, remember?

118
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,833
Ten?

119
00:05:17,667 --> 00:05:18,733
Me also.

120
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,933
You will also eat chilies?

121
00:05:28,567 --> 00:05:32,800
Wow! Your taro in coconut milk
smells delicious, Grandma Ikay.

122
00:05:32,867 --> 00:05:33,933
It has a lot of chilies.

123
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,667
That's my favourite.

124
00:05:35,767 --> 00:05:38,333
Oh really?

125
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,433
You are really
an Uragon, Celeste.

126
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,567
You are like Mikoy.

127
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,667
He also loves spicy food.

128
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:47,733
Grandma, I eat chilies
more than Celeste can.

129
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,800
Really?

130
00:05:48,867 --> 00:05:50,067
You should prove that.

131
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:51,767
You know even if you ask mother,

132
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:55,033
I'm the champion when it comes
to eating chilies.

133
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:56,667
Are you challenging me?

134
00:05:56,733 --> 00:05:58,067
It's up to you.

135
00:05:58,133 --> 00:05:59,567
You're brave.

136
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:03,333
- Here are the chilies.
- Hey, are you sure about that?

137
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,167
Don't worry, Grandma Ikay.

138
00:06:05,233 --> 00:06:06,233
I can do it.

139
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,633
I don't know about him.

140
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:08,667
Can you do it?

141
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:09,933
Here are the chilies.

142
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,433
Whoever gives up the first
time will treat ice cream.

143
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,933
- Game?
- Game.

144
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,433
Ready, set, go!

145
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:21,200
Oh my...

146
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:31,067
It's spicy!

147
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,067
It's so spicy.

148
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,100
Aren't you spiced up?

149
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,467
It's delicious.

150
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,800
What do you mean
it's delicious?

151
00:06:45,867 --> 00:06:47,700
- Look at me.
- You lost.

152
00:06:47,767 --> 00:06:50,533
- Hey, you kids.
-Hey, don't forget my ice cream.

153
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,700
Stop it.

154
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:52,867
You should drink milk.

155
00:06:54,167 --> 00:06:55,567
Drink.

156
00:06:55,633 --> 00:06:57,000
Wait.

157
00:06:57,067 --> 00:06:59,100
- You lost.
- Drink, drink.

158
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:00,133
Loser.

159
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:06,200
It's so spicy.

160
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:12,800
You're not even turning red?

161
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:14,767
I told you I always win.

162
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,200
This is very spicy, Grandma.

163
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:22,267
What?

164
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:26,433
Just finish it up.

165
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,600
Just a second.

166
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:28,933
It's still spicy?

167
00:07:35,433 --> 00:07:36,400
Just wait.

168
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:49,800
Can you still do it?

169
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:51,000
- One more.
- One more?

170
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:59,100
Celeste, you are silly.

171
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,400
One more.

172
00:08:10,467 --> 00:08:11,500
Huh?

173
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:14,300
What will I gain from this?

174
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,600
Grandma, water.

175
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,267
I'm sure Vivian has something
to do

176
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,733
with what your ex is doing.

177
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,967
Right from the very beginning,

178
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,333
she's pushing for you
to get back together.

179
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:16,700
Aurelia and I are just
friends, nothing more.

180
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:20,167
The question is...

181
00:09:20,233 --> 00:09:21,500
are you on the same page?

182
00:09:22,967 --> 00:09:24,100
What do you mean?

183
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,800
Tonito, the signs are clear.

184
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,900
Aurelia wants you back.

185
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:31,700
No woman will make an effort
like that

186
00:09:31,767 --> 00:09:34,167
if she doesn't like you.

187
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:38,067
She invested in your business
and she treated you for lunch.

188
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:42,900
You are really thinking
a lot of things.

189
00:09:42,967 --> 00:09:45,567
Stop playing naive, Tonito.

190
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,433
I know that you know
what I'm saying.

191
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:51,367
Just be careful.

192
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:55,600
That's the kind of person that
if you show a little kindness,

193
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:57,533
they will add malice to it.

194
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:00,467
So if I were you...

195
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:04,200
I'll set
healthy boundaries with her.

196
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:09,900
I already made it clear
to her that we're just friends

197
00:10:09,967 --> 00:10:11,633
for the sake of our daughter.

198
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:13,967
And she agreed to it.

199
00:10:14,033 --> 00:10:15,500
I just feel sorry
for Tiffany.

200
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:19,633
I hate to burst her bubble
but she has to accept

201
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,333
that Celeste and I
are getting married.

202
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,267
Hey...

203
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:51,433
what's happening?

204
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:56,967
Oh, come on!

205
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,300
Is that Aurelia?

206
00:11:29,433 --> 00:11:31,433
Yeah.

207
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:33,767
Healthy boundaries, Tonito.

208
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,800
Healthy boundaries.

209
00:11:35,867 --> 00:11:37,533
Hello, Aurelia?

210
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,200
Tonito...

211
00:11:39,267 --> 00:11:42,033
my car broke down.

212
00:11:42,133 --> 00:11:44,567
My driver is on a day off

213
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:47,067
and none of my friends
are answering my calls.

214
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:50,067
I need your help.

215
00:11:50,133 --> 00:11:51,400
Where are you?

216
00:11:51,467 --> 00:11:52,667
I'm still at the office.

217
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:06,467
Do you still
remember this?

218
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:08,233
Oh my, that's during the fiesta.

219
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:11,967
Yes, this is when you were
the Queen Emperatriz

220
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:13,933
at the May Festival.

221
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,267
Do you remember? I'm the one
who did your makeup.

222
00:12:16,367 --> 00:12:18,733
Because the makeup artist
didn't show up.

223
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:21,833
And you used glue on my hair

224
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:24,100
because we can't buy
a spray net.

225
00:12:24,167 --> 00:12:26,100
- Do you remember that?
- Yes.

226
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:27,167
I'm sorry.

227
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:29,000
It's okay. I had a hard time
removing that.

228
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:31,800
Oh my...

229
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:34,167
Hey, it's Mikoy.

230
00:12:34,233 --> 00:12:35,767
You're ugly here.

231
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:37,533
Look who's talking.
You were also not that beautiful

232
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,800
when you were a child.

233
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:41,100
That's why
I'm the Queen Emperatriz

234
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:44,533
and you carried the arc.

235
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,700
It's because Sir Patricio
was the Hermano Mayor.

236
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:48,833
So there's no other choice
that's why you were chosen.

237
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:50,200
Whatever.

238
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:53,033
This was during the picnic.

239
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:57,867
I arrived crying because
the bird that I found died.

240
00:12:57,933 --> 00:13:01,133
Ever since you really
have a soft heart.

241
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:04,367
Oh, just say
she's a cry baby.

242
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:06,433
That's what you call empathy.

243
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,967
Oh, this is the picture
of you and Mikoy

244
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:11,900
when you were still a couple.

245
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:16,300
Mmmm, this is fun.

246
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:19,533
This is when the two
of you were in Manila.

247
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,300
You sent this to me.

248
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,833
You said that this is where
you will take me

249
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,567
when I visit you.

250
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,100
It didn't push through.

251
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,567
Why are you still
keeping that, Grandma?

252
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:35,233
- Give that to me.
- Why?

253
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:36,567
I'm just showing it to her.

254
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:42,700
You know Celeste, I'm happy
for you

255
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:45,100
that you fulfilled your dreams
in Manila.

256
00:13:46,767 --> 00:13:50,667
You are very fluent in English
and Tagalog.

257
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:54,000
It's like you were born
in Manila.

258
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,667
Thank you, Grandma.

259
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,267
Celeste...

260
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:05,767
I know that you have forgotten
a lot about your past.

261
00:14:07,633 --> 00:14:10,367
Even if you have forgotten
in your mind,

262
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,800
but not in your heart.

263
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:17,867
It will take you home to
where you will be happy.

264
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:55,733
Aurelia?

265
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:56,767
Hi.

266
00:14:59,567 --> 00:15:00,733
I'll take you home.

267
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:03,067
Thank you.

268
00:15:39,033 --> 00:15:43,400
Thank you so much,
Grandma Ikay.

269
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:45,967
Thank you for the laughter
and the food.

270
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,933
I hope this is not the last.

271
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,800
Just come here
whenever you want.

272
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:53,767
You are always welcome here
anytime.

273
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:56,433
I have to go.

274
00:15:57,567 --> 00:16:00,067
- You take care.
- Okay.

275
00:16:00,133 --> 00:16:02,767
- Mikoy, drive carefully.
- Okay.

276
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:05,667
Thank you.

277
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,067
I'll just take her home,
Grandma.

278
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:10,633
Okay.

279
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:13,333
- Bye.
- Bye, Celeste.

280
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,200
You're very beautiful.

281
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Let's go.

282
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:32,267
Bye, thank you.

283
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:44,733
You should've checked
your car first

284
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,933
before you left the office.

285
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:50,367
But anyway that's not your job.

286
00:16:50,433 --> 00:16:52,467
Why did you drive alone
all of a sudden?

287
00:16:52,533 --> 00:16:53,500
Where is your driver?

288
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:57,533
You deserve my brother's love,
Aurelia.

289
00:17:02,867 --> 00:17:05,700
Aurelia, can you hear me?

290
00:17:05,767 --> 00:17:07,300
Huh?

291
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:09,133
Yeah.

292
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,433
Yeah.

293
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:13,733
Tonito...

294
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,567
did I make
your life miserable?

295
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:20,400
Aurelia, don't get me wrong.

296
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:22,900
I'm not upset
with what happened.

297
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:24,233
I'm just here to help.

298
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,233
But you could've avoided it
if...

299
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:28,133
No, that's not what I meant.

300
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,167
I'm not just talking about
what happened here tonight.

301
00:17:33,633 --> 00:17:35,633
Okay, so?

302
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:40,233
Are you and Celeste
really getting married?

303
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,033
Where is this coming from?

304
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,733
Are you sure about her?

305
00:17:48,933 --> 00:17:50,300
Without a doubt, yes.

306
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:52,800
Why?

307
00:17:53,933 --> 00:17:56,333
Aurelia, you're creeping me out.

308
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,533
Are you sure you're okay?

309
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,700
Maybe...

310
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:04,200
maybe not.

311
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:06,333
Just forget my questions.

312
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,167
I'm just playing...

313
00:18:08,233 --> 00:18:09,333
devil's advocate.

314
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,633
Thanks.

315
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,000
Okay.

316
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:15,500
I'll go ahead.
I'll show myself out.

317
00:18:17,467 --> 00:18:18,433
Good night.

318
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:58,667
Here we are.

319
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:05,333
- Tomorrow again?
- Yes.

320
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,000
Thank you, Mikoy.

321
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:11,867
I forgot how fun it is here
in Sorsogon and you reminded me

322
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:15,233
that in such a short amount
of time.

323
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:20,933
I left you sad in Manila then.

324
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:25,567
I'm just making
it up to you.

325
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:26,633
- Okay.
- Wait.

326
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:29,800
No, I can manage.

327
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,333
I'm not wearing heels.

328
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,367
Good night.

329
00:20:03,933 --> 00:20:06,567
No, no, I'll take care
of Celeste.

330
00:20:06,633 --> 00:20:08,933
Let me do it.

331
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,267
You should go home.
She is my responsibility.

332
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:12,833
- I'll take care of her.
- Miss Vangie?

333
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:13,833
No.

334
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:14,900
Don't talk anymore!

335
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:16,667
Wait, she's a woman.

336
00:20:16,733 --> 00:20:19,067
No, don't meddle.

337
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:20,367
I might get mad at you.

338
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,500
Go now.

339
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:25,733
Miss Vangie?

340
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:26,633
Don't beg!

341
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,267
Sorry.

342
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:33,333
Thank you.

343
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:39,467
- Hurry up.
- Ouch.

344
00:20:39,533 --> 00:20:40,567
Sorry.

345
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:45,000
She's terrible.

346
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,767
She's exaggerated.

347
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:49,433
She's too much.

348
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:51,467
Thank you for saving me today.

349
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:52,867
Thank you? There's a payment
for that.

350
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,433
What do you mean by payment?

351
00:21:00,933 --> 00:21:01,933
What's with you, Mikoy?

352
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,033
That's irritating.

353
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:06,700
Don't be like that. I'm getting
married, right?

354
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:08,167
So?

355
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,900
What do you mean so?

356
00:21:09,967 --> 00:21:11,100
Mikoy...

357
00:21:12,233 --> 00:21:14,933
you're not funny.

358
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:19,867
What do you think of me?
You know you're dirty-minded.

359
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:22,767
Anyway, where
will you take me?

360
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,500
Just wait.

361
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:25,667
Don't talk like that.

362
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:26,700
It's irritating.

363
00:21:30,633 --> 00:21:32,533
I'll take care of you.

364
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,000
- Trust me.
- No.

365
00:21:36,633 --> 00:21:41,100
Okay, I'll eat this
but you should eat ten chilies.

366
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:43,300
- Just ten?
- Yes.

367
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,433
Call.

368
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:54,433
Eat some more.

369
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,033
- It's ten, remember?
- Ten?

370
00:21:59,567 --> 00:22:03,100
I forgot how fun it is here
in Sorsogon

371
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:06,800
and you reminded me that in such
a short amount of time.

372
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:12,400
I left you sad
in Manila then.

373
00:22:12,467 --> 00:22:13,667
I'm just making it up to you.

374
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:17,567
Why is he doing all that?

375
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,667
There's only one
way to find out.

376
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,900
Hey...

377
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:04,300
what are you doing?

378
00:24:04,367 --> 00:24:06,900
- Nothing.
- Why are you smiling?

379
00:24:06,967 --> 00:24:08,667
It's beautiful.

380
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:09,800
What is beautiful?

381
00:24:09,867 --> 00:24:12,067
This book...

382
00:24:12,133 --> 00:24:14,200
it's thrilling. It's beautiful.

383
00:24:14,267 --> 00:24:18,733
When has a science book
become thrilling?

384
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:21,300
Let's just read.

385
00:24:21,367 --> 00:24:23,433
You read.

386
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,933
Yeah right!

387
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,633
No feelings will be rekindled.

388
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:31,867
Why is your nose like that?

389
00:25:31,933 --> 00:25:33,333
- What?
- It's growing long

390
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,033
because you are lying.

391
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,733
Welcome again to our farm.

392
00:25:36,833 --> 00:25:40,333
I told Mikoy not to make
your duty here hard for you.

393
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:42,733
- Oh no...
- Why?

394
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:45,267
Cynthia and Brooke got ahead
of us in the locations

395
00:25:45,333 --> 00:25:47,067
and products that we researched.

396
00:25:47,133 --> 00:25:48,333
Tiff...

397
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:50,500
Do you know how to break
a pili nut?

398
00:25:50,567 --> 00:25:53,933
My mother taught me
when I was young so I know.

399
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,167
I can work alone.

400
00:25:55,233 --> 00:25:57,200
What's good about Celeste
is that she knows

401
00:25:57,267 --> 00:25:59,100
how to love someone
without being pushy.

402
00:25:59,167 --> 00:26:01,667
I'm really from here.

403
00:26:01,733 --> 00:26:02,967
Basti is my boyfriend.

404
00:26:03,033 --> 00:26:04,000
Yes, Sir.

405
00:26:04,067 --> 00:26:05,933
They don't take outsiders here.

406
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,133
I know what you're saying.

407
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,933
It's your excuse just to flirt
with him.

408
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:12,333
You are an opportunist.

409
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,100
- James.
- Am I the one who thought that?

410
00:26:14,167 --> 00:26:17,633
I have had enough
of this crap.

411
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:20,667
You know maybe it's time
that all of you should know

412
00:26:20,733 --> 00:26:24,033
how insensitive you all are.

413
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:27,200
I've been hurting
for almost half of my life

414
00:26:27,267 --> 00:26:28,700
because of all of you!

415
00:26:28,767 --> 00:26:31,133
She loves her father deeply.

416
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:35,033
The deeper the love,
the deeper the anger.

417
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:40,067
Sometimes that anger
will blind you

418
00:26:40,133 --> 00:26:42,467
until your heart becomes numb.

419
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:44,167
You're not telling me the truth.

420
00:26:44,233 --> 00:26:45,967
I don't know why
you think that way.

421
00:26:46,033 --> 00:26:47,200
Do you still love me?

422
00:26:51,400 --> 00:26:52,400
Yes or no.

423
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,200
Do you still love me, Mikoy?
